VVocal concert by Palani Gnanasakthivel marked the 52nd monthly music festival of the Tiruchi Tamizh Isai Sangam held in Tiruchi  recently. He was accompanied  by Thanjavur Janakiraman (violin), Thanjavur Sankarasubramanian (mridangam) and Pudukottai \u000aGopi Krishna (ganjira). The divisional railway manager, S. Subrahmanyan, was the chief guest.  Speaking on the occasion he explained the ancient glory and richness of Tamil music. &#8220;There is a strong need for conserving the treasure of Tamil music so that it  benefits posterity in the long run,&#8221; Subrahmanyan added.The vice-president of the Sangam, N. Mohan, presided over the function, while its secretary K. Arangarajan, Shafi Ahmed, industrialist and others offered felicitations.
